    <node id="logic_rule_81f3ac2179bef2ead787e5ae7cf79591">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If a book is well-catalogued, then it is available. -&gt; ∀x (W(x) → A(x))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["W"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["A"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_693eae01e4dde1068d746abe042bc2bf">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If a book is in good condition, then it is well-catalogued. -&gt; ∀x (G(x) → W(x))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["G"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["W"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_c8bb20ad9043a8dc1e0dba10673d48e2">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If a book is well-catalogued, then it is recommended. -&gt; ∀x (W(x) → R(x))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["W"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["R"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_eac8ab94c135265cd72c44530bc5ccd4">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If a book is not available, then it is not well-catalogued. -&gt; ∀x (¬A(x) → ¬W(x))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["\u00acA"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["\u00acW"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_fba549d7c30298285c723796714bd69e">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If a book is available, then it is in good condition. -&gt; ∀x (∀ x (A(x) → G(x)))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["A"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["G"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_881aaf031c0e9665d637f07e07355db0">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If a book is not in high demand, then it is not available. -&gt; ∀x (¬H(x) → ¬A(x))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["\u00acH"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["\u00acA"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_c0f29bb9bcf39b89cb3f55a9c4878f51">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If a book is not in good condition, then it is not well-catalogued. -&gt; ∀x (¬G(x) → ¬W(x))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["\u00acG"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["\u00acW"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_f2ffbb0c1d5ae2c0dcabc575ca028be9">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If a book is not frequently borrowed, then it is not in good condition. -&gt; ∀x (¬F(x) → ¬G(x))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["\u00acF"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["\u00acG"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_6204ef87bada2539e312f37538d369a9">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If a book is frequently borrowed, then it is recommended. -&gt; ∀x (F(x) → R(x))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["F"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["R"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_ecaf44812eb1d42d7c1a0875225e3756">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If a book is frequently borrowed, then it is well-catalogued. -&gt; ∀x (F(x) → W(x))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["F"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["W"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_b20f46e9f86fa08964420607e66b604d">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If a book is recommended, then it is in good condition. -&gt; ∀x (R(x) → G(x))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["R"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["G"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_98e47ad2311c9fe8193ede60f072b0eb">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If a book is not available, then it is not frequently borrowed. -&gt; ∀x (¬A(x) → ¬F(x))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["\u00acA"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["\u00acF"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_d2f0f7081286e735a04ad3c3e22771d9">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If not being in high demand implies a book is not available, then if a book is not available, it is not frequently borrowed. -&gt; ∀x (¬H(x) → ¬A(x)) → ∀x (¬A(x) → ¬F(x))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["\u00acH", "\u00acA"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["\u00acA", "\u00acF"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_887a7aa9855a32cc40aab2052736fa66">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If being frequently borrowed implies a book is well-catalogued, then if a book is not available, it is not well-catalogued. -&gt; ∀x (F(x) → W(x)) → ∀x (¬A(x) → ¬W(x))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["F", "W"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["A", "W"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_11882747b0d5fec2724ee8007db801f4">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If every book is available, then every book is frequently borrowed. -&gt; ∀x A(x) → ∀x F(x)</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["A"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["F"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_f53f43ccbd071f2517d613af0e8a4bd3">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If the fact that frequently borrowed books are well-catalogued implies that unavailable books are not well-catalogued, then every book is in high demand. -&gt; (∀x (F(x) → W(x)) → ∀x (¬A(x) → ¬W(x))) → ∀x H(x)</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["\u2200x (F(x) \u2192 W(x))", "\u2200x (\u00acA(x) \u2192 \u00acW(x))"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["\u2200x H(x)"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_6d9afef98f42cc0e985bc66832fef8b6">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If having a good condition implies a book is well-catalogued, then if frequently borrowed books are well-catalogued, an unavailable book is not well-catalogued. -&gt; ∀x (G(x) → W(x)) → (∀x (F(x) → W(x)) → ∀x (¬A(x) → ¬W(x)))</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
      <data key="d3">["G", "F"]</data>
      <data key="d4">["A", "W"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="logic_rule_338055618e5d6255228d3d9c0305249d">
      <data key="d0">Pattern: If the previous implication holds, then every book is in good condition. -&gt; (∀x (G(x) → W(x)) → (∀x (F(x) → W(x)) → ∀x (¬A(x) → ¬W(x)))) → ∀x G(x)</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d1">True</data>
